Questions:
What is the primary objective of the research study involving Tranexamic Acid (TXA) in patients undergoing limb salvage surgery for bone sarcoma?
A) To compare the effectiveness of TXA against a placebo in reducing postoperative pain;
B) To assess the impact of TXA on the speed of bone healing after surgery;
C) To evaluate the efficacy of TXA in preventing postoperative blood loss and associated complications;
D) To determine the cost-effectiveness of using TXA in all surgical procedures.

Correct answer: C

What are your options if you choose not to participate in the Tranexamic Acid study for bone sarcoma patients undergoing limb salvage surgery?
A) You will be required to undergo an alternative experimental treatment; 
B) Your surgery will be postponed until you agree to participate;
C) You will receive the standard care and surgical plan previously discussed with your surgeon and anesthesiologist;
D) You will not receive any surgical treatment for your condition.

Correct answer: C

How will your personal information be handled in the study regarding the efficacy of Tranexamic Acid in bone sarcoma patients?
A) Information will be shared publicly for educational purposes;
B) Information will be stored in a locker cabinet accessible only to investigators and submitted to the hospital Clinical Research Office;
C) Information will be disclosed to all hospital staff members;
D) Personal information will be used for marketing purposes.

Correct answer: B

If you have concerns or questions about your rights as a participant in this study, whom should you contact?

A) The Secretary, Institutional Review Board at SKMCH & RC;
B) The Principal Investigator of the study;
C) The hospital's general information desk;
D) Your personal physician.

Correct answer: A) The Secretary, Institutional Review Board at SKMCH & RC;
